          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Changing of the guard</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/gp-dec-25-2.jpg" alt="Changing of the guard" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Romania’s parliament has <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-25-dec-2024-4-approved" target="_blank">approved</a> a new pro-European coalition government led by Prime Minister Marcel Ciolacu, aiming to resolve a political crisis triggered by far-right gains and the <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-25-dec-2024-5-annulment" target="_blank">annulment</a> of a presidential election. The coalition includes the Social Democratic Party (PSD), National Liberal Party (PNL), UDMR, and national minorities, holding a slim majority. Ciolacu acknowledged the challenges ahead, including economic struggles and public mistrust, and pledged to organize a rerun of the annulled presidential race quickly.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Far-right leader George Simion and his party opposed the coalition, reflecting rising nationalist sentiment amid high living costs. Analysts predict the coalition will use moderate populist rhetoric to counter far-right influence while maintaining a pro-European stance. President Klaus Iohannis warned of a difficult period as the new government seeks to rebuild trust and stability.​</p>
        </mj-text>
