          Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-25-dec-2024-9-accused" target="_blank">accused</a> Slovak Prime Minister Robert Fico of aiding Moscow's war effort and undermining Europe's energy independence after Fico met with Russian President Vladimir Putin to discuss gas supplies. Zelensky criticized Fico's pro-Russian policies, calling them a "big security issue" and alleging they involved murky schemes and compromises to sovereignty. He also claimed Fico seeks to push American gas and partner energy resources away from Europe, indirectly funding Putin's war.</p>
